cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.SY 

This paper deals with the verification of information flow security properties in the context of compilers and concurrent programs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves formal methods and programming languages, which suggests cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) as likely categories. The paper also deals with concurrency, which suggests cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as possible categories.
